The paper deals with the design of full-duplex relay systems, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of multiple antennas, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes an algorithmic framework, which involves optimization and control theory, and hence, it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of MIMO technology, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms, which could be evaluated using machine learning techniques, and hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
